1
00:00:12,012 --> 00:00:14,139
-Good evening.
-Good evening.

2
00:00:14,222 --> 00:00:16,892
<i>Terrace House</i> is a show about
six strangers, men and women,

3
00:00:16,975 --> 00:00:18,519
6 STRANGERS, MEN AND WOMEN,
SHARE A HOUSE.

4
00:00:18,602 --> 00:00:21,271
living together, and we observe
how they interact with each other.

5
00:00:21,354 --> 00:00:23,899
<i>All that we've prepared is</i>
<i>a beautiful home and automobile.</i>

6
00:00:23,982 --> 00:00:26,985
-There is no script at all.
-Yes.

7
00:00:27,069 --> 00:00:31,156
Last week, Minori and Uchi...

8
00:00:31,239 --> 00:00:34,702
-left the house.
-That's right.

9
00:00:34,785 --> 00:00:36,662
<i>It was a tearful goodbye.</i>

10
00:00:36,745 --> 00:00:38,664
<i>It finally felt like</i>
<i>everyone was under one roof.</i>

11
00:00:38,747 --> 00:00:42,125
<i>Some warmth was finally back</i>
<i>at</i> Terrace House.

12
00:00:42,209 --> 00:00:44,503
This was all thanks to the meat incident.

13
00:00:44,587 --> 00:00:46,004
That's true.

14
00:00:46,797 --> 00:00:48,966
Meat can do so many things.

15
00:00:49,049 --> 00:00:50,926
It's not just delicious.

16
00:00:52,928 --> 00:00:54,972
And if they left, that means...

17
00:00:55,055 --> 00:00:58,726
-Misaki's arrival.
-That's right. Tamosan is here.

18
00:00:58,809 --> 00:01:01,770
-I'm sorry, what was your name again?
-I'm Misaki Tamori.

19
00:01:01,854 --> 00:01:03,105
-Misaki?
-Misaki.

20
00:01:03,188 --> 00:01:05,858
My friends call me Tamochan or Tamosan.

21
00:01:05,941 --> 00:01:06,942
Tamosan?

22
00:01:07,025 --> 00:01:08,944
-Super cute?
-Yeah?

23
00:01:09,027 --> 00:01:10,112
Your type?

24
00:01:10,195 --> 00:01:12,197
-She's pretty high energy.
-Yeah.

25
00:01:12,280 --> 00:01:13,699
I love that.

26
00:01:14,491 --> 00:01:17,077
Dreams for the future?
We haven't asked that yet.

27
00:01:17,160 --> 00:01:18,203
An amusement park.

28
00:01:18,286 --> 00:01:19,287
-To build one?
-Yes.

29
00:01:19,371 --> 00:01:23,208
-An amusement park of everyone's dreams.
-That's right!

30
00:01:23,291 --> 00:01:26,003
<i>-A pretty girl.</i>
<i>-Yes, very beautiful.</i>

31
00:01:26,086 --> 00:01:29,673
-Her dream is to build an amusement park.
-Yeah.

32
00:01:29,757 --> 00:01:31,967
Didn't you know someone like that
as a kid?

33
00:01:32,050 --> 00:01:35,345
"When I build it,
I'll do your store, too!"

34
00:01:35,428 --> 00:01:37,765
It's a little strange to say
after you turn 20, though.

35
00:01:38,516 --> 00:01:39,642
That's right.

36
00:01:39,725 --> 00:01:42,185
-The new guy is coming today.
-Yes, that's right!

37
00:01:42,269 --> 00:01:44,479
-He seems mature.
-Very mature.

38
00:01:44,563 --> 00:01:47,482
I'm very interested to see
what he looks like.

39
00:01:47,566 --> 00:01:50,318
What made you decide?

40
00:01:50,402 --> 00:01:52,655
I'm graduating...

41
00:01:52,738 --> 00:01:54,573
I figured it'd be a good change of pace.

42
00:01:54,657 --> 00:01:57,117
-Seems like the smart type.
-Yes.

43
00:01:57,200 --> 00:01:59,662
-That's what's nice.
-I want to see his face.

44
00:01:59,745 --> 00:02:02,665
-I want to see his face. Let's watch.
-Shall we watch?

45
00:02:10,422 --> 00:02:12,550
I'm really nervous for some reason.

46
00:02:12,633 --> 00:02:14,760
Maybe because it's so sudden.

47
00:02:14,843 --> 00:02:18,305
-Wow.
-What do you mean, "Wow"?

48
00:02:18,388 --> 00:02:21,058
-It's nice to meet you.
-Nice to meet you.

49
00:02:21,141 --> 00:02:22,267
I'm Handa.

50
00:02:22,851 --> 00:02:24,520
It's nice to meet you.

51
00:02:25,270 --> 00:02:26,772
-Kanda?
-Kanda.

52
00:02:27,856 --> 00:02:29,482
What was your name again?

53
00:02:29,567 --> 00:02:30,943
-Handa.
-Oh, Handa.

54
00:02:31,026 --> 00:02:34,321
-I'm Yuto Handa. It's nice to meet you.
-Nice to meet you.

55
00:02:34,404 --> 00:02:36,949
-What do you do?
-How old are you?

56
00:02:38,075 --> 00:02:40,243
I'm currently still in university...

57
00:02:40,327 --> 00:02:43,747
-You're a student?
-I'm graduating in March.

58
00:02:43,831 --> 00:02:46,542
I major in architecture
at Tokyo University of the Arts.

59
00:02:46,625 --> 00:02:51,505
I'm studying architecture.
I'm 27, trying to become an architect.

60
00:02:53,006 --> 00:02:54,216
-He's older!
-He's older!

61
00:02:54,299 --> 00:02:56,927
-You seem happy.
-You're super happy.

62
00:02:57,010 --> 00:02:59,638
If you study architecture,
do you also design?

63
00:02:59,722 --> 00:03:01,473
-Yes.
-Design?

64
00:03:01,557 --> 00:03:03,642
Mainly designing and drafting, too.

65
00:03:03,726 --> 00:03:10,232
I've been taking outside projects
such as renovating and designing cafés.

66
00:03:10,315 --> 00:03:13,193
I'll continue to do it
and work independently.

67
00:03:13,276 --> 00:03:14,778
With tools.

68
00:03:14,862 --> 00:03:17,072
-You do it all yourself?
-I do.

69
00:03:17,155 --> 00:03:18,657
-Wow.
-Not the best results.

70
00:03:18,741 --> 00:03:21,660
-Oh, then he can make my amusement park.
-Amusement park?

71
00:03:21,744 --> 00:03:23,746
-It's her dream.
-She wants you to design it.

72
00:03:23,829 --> 00:03:27,040
Design an amusement park?
Sounds difficult.

73
00:03:27,124 --> 00:03:30,002
-The dream is big.
-The dream is huge.

74
00:03:30,085 --> 00:03:32,004
Why did you come to <i>Terrace House?</i>

75
00:03:32,087 --> 00:03:34,590
I'm graduating,
but I don't plan on looking for a job.

76
00:03:34,673 --> 00:03:39,011
I plan to spend this year preparing
to study abroad.

77
00:03:39,094 --> 00:03:42,765
Is there a specific school in mind?
A school you're hoping to get into?

78
00:03:43,516 --> 00:03:46,977
I'm aiming for Harvard in Boston.

79
00:03:47,060 --> 00:03:49,312
-That's my first choice.
-Harvard?

80
00:03:49,396 --> 00:03:51,439
-Harvard Architecture? That's impressive.
-Wow.

81
00:03:51,524 --> 00:03:56,194
Yes, if I can get in.
Otherwise, maybe Columbia.

82
00:03:56,278 --> 00:04:00,240
-You must be really smart.
-Not at all.

83
00:04:00,323 --> 00:04:03,577
What do you need to do to get in?
Know English?

84
00:04:03,661 --> 00:04:08,916
English, a portfolio of my work,
and an interview.

85
00:04:08,999 --> 00:04:10,375
What about studying?

86
00:04:10,458 --> 00:04:13,170
I do have to study a little.

87
00:04:13,253 --> 00:04:14,547
A little bit.

88
00:04:14,630 --> 00:04:17,465
So you finished school,
but you want to go back?

89
00:04:17,550 --> 00:04:19,843
Yes. Graduate school.

90
00:04:19,927 --> 00:04:21,386
-Wow.
-For a master's degree.

91
00:04:21,469 --> 00:04:23,681
-Do you have a girlfriend?
-I do.

92
00:04:23,764 --> 00:04:25,390
-You do?
-Yes.

93
00:04:25,473 --> 00:04:27,518
-Where? I mean, not where...
-Where?

94
00:04:29,436 --> 00:04:30,813
How long have you been together?

95
00:04:30,896 --> 00:04:33,524
-A little over two years.
-Oh, a long time.

96
00:04:33,607 --> 00:04:35,275
How old is she?

97
00:04:35,358 --> 00:04:38,612
She's turning... 23, I think.

98
00:04:38,696 --> 00:04:41,615
-She didn't oppose to your moving here?
-That's right.

99
00:04:42,199 --> 00:04:47,538
She did a little bit,
but she sent me off in good spirits.

100
00:04:47,621 --> 00:04:49,497
-Do you drink?
-What?

101
00:04:49,582 --> 00:04:51,875
-Do you drink?
-Yes, I do.

102
00:04:51,959 --> 00:04:53,085
That's good.

103
00:04:53,168 --> 00:04:55,337
Would you like a drink now? No?

104
00:04:55,420 --> 00:04:57,965
Sure. Is that okay?

105
00:04:58,048 --> 00:05:01,594
-Have you had dinner yet?
-Only a little.

106
00:05:01,677 --> 00:05:03,804
-There's curry.
-Curry?

107
00:05:03,887 --> 00:05:06,181
Sure, I'd love some.

108
00:05:07,516 --> 00:05:09,852
-Here you go.
-Thank you.

109
00:05:12,187 --> 00:05:13,522
I'm gonna get water.

110
00:05:13,606 --> 00:05:16,358
What do you think of...
Oh, you've only seen the living room.

111
00:05:16,441 --> 00:05:18,276
-Yes.
-Me, too.

112
00:05:18,360 --> 00:05:21,572
The exterior surprised me, though.
It's huge!

113
00:05:21,655 --> 00:05:24,449
Right, this is right up your alley.
Are you looking around?

114
00:05:24,533 --> 00:05:27,244
I'm planning on taking
a closer look at the details later.

115
00:05:27,327 --> 00:05:28,704
Details? What details?

116
00:05:28,787 --> 00:05:30,873
-Oh, the finer points around the--
-Here you go.

117
00:05:30,956 --> 00:05:34,042
Thank you.
That's a big serving.

118
00:05:34,126 --> 00:05:35,210
Is it?

119
00:05:35,293 --> 00:05:37,880
I'm used to serving Hikaru.
I thought maybe that's not enough.

120
00:05:37,963 --> 00:05:39,757
I can totally eat.

121
00:05:39,840 --> 00:05:41,091
-Can I go ahead?
-Of course.

122
00:05:41,174 --> 00:05:42,175
Thank you.

123
00:05:46,221 --> 00:05:47,305
It's delicious.

124
00:05:47,389 --> 00:05:49,349
Do you like to keep things clean?

125
00:05:49,432 --> 00:05:50,893
-Nope.
-Not at all?

126
00:05:50,976 --> 00:05:52,227
I'm super messy.

127
00:05:52,310 --> 00:05:53,646
Super messy?

128
00:05:54,772 --> 00:05:56,857
So besides Natsumi,
does anyone else keep clean?

129
00:05:56,940 --> 00:05:59,234
She just came in,
so I don't know how bad she is.

130
00:05:59,317 --> 00:06:02,445
-I think it's pretty bad.
-You seem like you'd be messy.

131
00:06:04,657 --> 00:06:06,241
Maybe that was rude.

132
00:06:06,324 --> 00:06:08,952
Of course I'll keep clean, though.
It's a co-op after all.

133
00:06:09,036 --> 00:06:11,914
Yay! I'm glad.
Let's do it together.

134
00:06:11,997 --> 00:06:13,957
How long have you been together
with your girlfriend?

135
00:06:14,041 --> 00:06:17,210
This is the second time you've asked,
but two and a half years.

136
00:06:19,713 --> 00:06:21,423
He's so mature.

137
00:06:21,507 --> 00:06:23,091
The way he answered that.

138
00:06:24,552 --> 00:06:26,219
Two and a half years, huh?

139
00:06:27,387 --> 00:06:30,098
It's that complicated point
in a relationship.

140
00:06:30,933 --> 00:06:33,226
-That's your opinion.
-You said that earlier, too.

141
00:06:35,896 --> 00:06:38,106
That's true.
It can be complicated.

142
00:06:38,190 --> 00:06:39,983
-Especially during spring time.
-Right?

143
00:06:40,901 --> 00:06:42,319
What do you mean, "Right"?

144
00:06:42,945 --> 00:06:45,238
What are your plans tomorrow?

145
00:06:45,322 --> 00:06:47,324
My friend just got married.

146
00:06:48,033 --> 00:06:52,705
He asked me to build a table for him,
so I need to work on that.

147
00:06:52,788 --> 00:06:54,790
Do you have tools with you?

148
00:06:54,873 --> 00:06:57,000
-I have a lot.
-Really?

149
00:06:57,084 --> 00:06:58,586
Where do you keep it?

150
00:06:58,669 --> 00:07:01,589
I keep it at the studio.

151
00:07:01,672 --> 00:07:03,298
-You have a studio?
-Yes.

152
00:07:03,381 --> 00:07:05,217
Where is it?

153
00:07:05,300 --> 00:07:07,302
We're asking so many questions.

154
00:07:07,385 --> 00:07:09,012
Where is it?

155
00:07:09,096 --> 00:07:12,641
Um, near Ueno.
Near the school.

156
00:07:18,856 --> 00:07:22,568
He was nice enough
to pick up the trash here.

157
00:07:22,651 --> 00:07:24,319
I thought maybe I dropped it.

158
00:07:24,402 --> 00:07:27,489
Isn't that hardened leftover noodles?

159
00:07:27,573 --> 00:07:29,700
-Hardened noodles?
-When is that from?

160
00:07:29,783 --> 00:07:32,494
-I don't know.
-That's true. It's a little hard.

161
00:07:32,578 --> 00:07:33,787
It's hard?

162
00:07:33,871 --> 00:07:38,000
-I like that about him.
-He made your heart flutter?

163
00:07:38,083 --> 00:07:40,168
I'll show you the rooms.

164
00:07:40,252 --> 00:07:42,254
Can I put my luggage away?

165
00:07:42,337 --> 00:07:44,047
-Me, too.
-That's right.

166
00:07:44,131 --> 00:07:46,341
I'll wash this later.

167
00:07:46,424 --> 00:07:48,385
You're so sweet!

168
00:07:48,468 --> 00:07:50,763
-Well, I'm the one who ate it.
-I'm impressed.

169
00:07:51,764 --> 00:07:53,098
Oh, thank you.

170
00:07:53,181 --> 00:07:55,392
-Is this it?
-Yes, that's it.

171
00:07:55,475 --> 00:07:57,019
I'll lead the way.

172
00:08:16,038 --> 00:08:18,791
ARMAN BITARAF, 25 YEARS OLD,
ASPIRING FIREFIGHTER

173
00:08:18,874 --> 00:08:21,794
ARISA OHATA, 25 YEARS OLD,
HAT DESIGNER

174
00:08:21,877 --> 00:08:24,922
HIKARU OTA, 18 YEARS OLD,
MODEL, CONSTRUCTION WORKER

175
00:08:25,005 --> 00:08:27,883
NATSUMI SAITO, 26 YEARS OLD,
MODEL, ASPIRING ACTRESS

176
00:08:27,966 --> 00:08:31,094
YUTO HANDA, 27 YEARS OLD,
4TH YEAR AT TOKYO UNIVERSITY OF THE ARTS

177
00:08:31,178 --> 00:08:34,640
MISAKI TAMORI, 23 YEARS OLD,
ASPIRING ENTERTAINER, PART-TIMER

178
00:08:46,318 --> 00:08:48,403
-Is that a traditional-style tattoo?
-Yeah.

179
00:08:48,486 --> 00:08:50,030
-It's really cool.
-Thanks.

180
00:08:50,113 --> 00:08:53,325
It had been just completed.
Added the color.

181
00:08:53,408 --> 00:08:55,118
What are you working on right now?

182
00:08:55,202 --> 00:08:58,581
My priority right now is the café project.

183
00:08:59,497 --> 00:09:01,333
-The...
-You're doing the interior?

184
00:09:01,416 --> 00:09:03,627
-The exterior.
-The exterior?

185
00:09:03,711 --> 00:09:05,796
They asked for a more stylish exterior,

186
00:09:05,879 --> 00:09:09,508
so that anyone would recognize it
as a café.

187
00:09:09,592 --> 00:09:10,759
That was the request.

188
00:09:10,843 --> 00:09:13,470
It's about 80% done.

189
00:09:13,554 --> 00:09:16,807
It's really small, so it's quick.
Well, it was supposed to be.

190
00:09:16,890 --> 00:09:18,976
But more requests came up.

191
00:09:19,059 --> 00:09:22,896
So I'm just finishing some details.
Things like re-painting.

192
00:09:22,980 --> 00:09:24,773
I'll be happy to help.

193
00:09:24,857 --> 00:09:27,400
-There's a lot I need help with.
-Of course.

194
00:09:27,484 --> 00:09:30,904
-I can help paint at least.
-Yeah, that'll be great!

195
00:09:30,988 --> 00:09:33,866
Is there something you want
to accomplish at <i>Terrace House?</i>

196
00:09:33,949 --> 00:09:37,620
I didn't come here with any clear goals.

197
00:09:37,703 --> 00:09:40,288
I consider it an adventure.

198
00:09:40,831 --> 00:09:42,457
I don't know what'll happen.

199
00:09:42,541 --> 00:09:46,128
I just thought
something new would come out of it.

200
00:09:46,211 --> 00:09:50,090
I don't think there are too many people
in co-ed living situations.

201
00:09:50,173 --> 00:09:54,845
I thought it could be fun.
Not just as friends, you know?

202
00:09:54,928 --> 00:09:58,516
-So you'd be mad if it was messy here.
-No.

203
00:09:58,599 --> 00:10:01,935
This much is okay?
Of course, of course!

204
00:10:02,853 --> 00:10:06,982
But leaving cups out all dried up...

205
00:10:07,065 --> 00:10:08,567
That's not me.

206
00:10:08,651 --> 00:10:10,819
No, I think it's you.

207
00:10:12,070 --> 00:10:15,198
It's your first day,
but I feel so comfortable with you.

208
00:10:15,282 --> 00:10:16,283
Yeah?

209
00:10:17,660 --> 00:10:21,038
Probably because you girls are so nice.

210
00:10:21,121 --> 00:10:22,915
-Yeah!
-I think that's why.

211
00:10:24,625 --> 00:10:26,669
-What about the guys?
-The guys...

212
00:10:27,586 --> 00:10:29,129
They're nice, too.

213
00:10:29,922 --> 00:10:32,424
-But a little scary?
-Not scary--

214
00:10:32,508 --> 00:10:35,427
-I feel like Hikaru might explode someday.
-That's true.

215
00:10:36,512 --> 00:10:39,097
I didn't think
a guy would also come today.

216
00:10:39,181 --> 00:10:40,473
Me neither.

217
00:10:41,141 --> 00:10:42,976
-But he has a girlfriend.
-Oh, yeah.

218
00:10:43,060 --> 00:10:44,728
I forgot.

219
00:10:44,812 --> 00:10:46,897
-That's right.
-I was so surprised.

220
00:10:46,980 --> 00:10:49,066
-It was a surprise.
-Wasn't it?

221
00:10:49,149 --> 00:10:51,234
He seems really nice.

222
00:10:51,318 --> 00:10:54,112
-He seems mature.
-But dirty.

223
00:10:54,196 --> 00:10:56,448
-Dirty?
-No, that's not what I meant.

224
00:10:56,532 --> 00:10:59,284
He said he didn't like to clean.

225
00:10:59,367 --> 00:11:02,412
But when he picked up that trash...

226
00:11:02,495 --> 00:11:05,123
-I'm sure he's a cleaner.
-Really?

227
00:11:05,207 --> 00:11:08,001
-He was just being modest?
-Yeah, he knows how to be modest.

228
00:11:08,502 --> 00:11:09,962
Hansan...

229
00:11:11,088 --> 00:11:12,089
I wonder...

230
00:11:12,172 --> 00:11:14,341
He's got a girlfriend, you know?

231
00:11:16,802 --> 00:11:18,596
But you never know.

232
00:11:18,679 --> 00:11:20,806
They might break up.
They'll probably break up.

233
00:11:20,889 --> 00:11:22,725
They're probably gonna break up?

234
00:11:22,808 --> 00:11:24,602
Well, I don't know, but...

235
00:11:24,685 --> 00:11:28,021
It doesn't matter if he has a girlfriend.

236
00:11:29,064 --> 00:11:30,941
If I fall for him, that is.

237
00:11:31,024 --> 00:11:32,985
-Seriously?
-It doesn't matter at all.

238
00:11:34,277 --> 00:11:37,114
Oh, man.
Mr. Perfect is here.

239
00:11:39,032 --> 00:11:41,409
What? Is that the chat room opinion?

240
00:11:42,160 --> 00:11:44,079
The voice of the chat rooms.

241
00:11:44,162 --> 00:11:46,414
I can't believe Mr. Perfect is here.

242
00:11:48,501 --> 00:11:50,753
-A real good one arrived.
-Yeah.

