-Do you have a lot of free time?
-Yeah, I'm pretty free.

491
00:23:16,647 --> 00:23:18,481
-Have you seen my motorcycle downstairs?
-I did.

492
00:23:18,566 --> 00:23:20,150
I was wondering whose it was.

493
00:23:20,233 --> 00:23:22,653
It's mine.
You can ride it.

494
00:23:22,736 --> 00:23:25,030
I can't.
I don't have a license.

495
00:23:26,532 --> 00:23:29,117
It's scary riding the back.

496
00:23:29,201 --> 00:23:33,163
-It's not scary with me.
-I think I'd definitely be scared.

497
00:23:33,246 --> 00:23:36,709
-I might speed up on purpose though.
-I think you would.

498
00:23:36,792 --> 00:23:38,669
I'm just kidding.

499
00:23:38,752 --> 00:23:42,005
I seriously want you to ride with me.
Just normally.

500
00:23:43,799 --> 00:23:45,342
I'm scared though.

501
00:23:55,603 --> 00:23:58,480
-Is it cleaner than usual in here?
-Yeah.

502
00:24:01,233 --> 00:24:05,153
Earlier, when Nacchan and I went upstairs,
what did you guys talk about?

503
00:24:05,237 --> 00:24:08,031
I was planning on asking her out.

504
00:24:09,032 --> 00:24:11,493
Like, "Let's go somewhere."

505
00:24:11,577 --> 00:24:14,747
I was planning to, but... I couldn't.

506
00:24:14,830 --> 00:24:18,000
I couldn't find the right opening.

507
00:24:18,083 --> 00:24:19,960
It was kind of difficult.

508
00:24:20,043 --> 00:24:23,046
I did say,
"Let's go somewhere on my bike."

509
00:24:23,964 --> 00:24:25,758
Or that's what I meant to say.

510
00:24:26,759 --> 00:24:28,677
But I don't think she got it.

511
00:24:29,553 --> 00:24:32,347
I think it's fine to just ask.

512
00:24:33,306 --> 00:24:35,225
But she did say
she wanted to ride the bike.

513
00:24:35,308 --> 00:24:36,852
-She did?
-Yeah.

514
00:24:36,935 --> 00:24:39,897
She said that but you didn't ask then?

515
00:24:41,106 --> 00:24:43,567
I asked if she wanted to ride with me.

516
00:24:43,651 --> 00:24:45,318
You didn't say, "Let's go somewhere"?

517
00:24:45,402 --> 00:24:46,820
Well...

518
00:24:46,904 --> 00:24:50,699
maybe I just didn't say it right.

519
00:24:51,575 --> 00:24:53,285
-Just ask her casually.
-Casually?

520
00:24:53,368 --> 00:24:55,370
Yeah, casually.
You know, normally.

521
00:24:56,705 --> 00:24:58,666
Like, "Let's go somewhere together"?

522
00:24:58,749 --> 00:25:00,876
-On the bike?
-On the bike.

523
00:25:00,959 --> 00:25:04,296
"You said you wanted to ride,
so let's go somewhere."

524
00:25:04,379 --> 00:25:06,507
Nice. Sounds fun.

525
00:25:06,590 --> 00:25:10,177
-Should I ask her now?
-Now or sometime soon.

526
00:25:10,260 --> 00:25:13,681
-It's fresh now. She may forget later.
-She might forget.

527
00:25:13,764 --> 00:25:16,809
It's like I'm Yuki.
I don't like it.

528
00:25:16,892 --> 00:25:19,269
Well, everyone has their own timing.

529
00:25:20,270 --> 00:25:22,355
I should do it today.

530
00:25:23,732 --> 00:25:28,361
So he takes everyone to his studio...

531
00:25:28,445 --> 00:25:30,656
He's so cool.
It was a good move.

532
00:25:30,739 --> 00:25:34,993
-You seem happy.
-Very happy.

533
00:25:35,077 --> 00:25:38,539
And his motivation, that was 100 points.

534
00:25:38,622 --> 00:25:39,832
It was 100 points.

535
00:25:39,915 --> 00:25:43,251
He built something when he was a kid,
and he couldn't forget how fun it was.

536
00:25:43,335 --> 00:25:47,464
He went to college to study,
but he still wanted to try.

537
00:25:47,548 --> 00:25:50,634
And then he's able to get
into Tokyo University of the Arts.

538
00:25:50,718 --> 00:25:51,927
-Right?
-Right?

539
00:25:52,010 --> 00:25:55,388
From School of Education
at Waseda University.

540
00:25:55,472 --> 00:25:58,266
-And he never mentions it.
-He doesn't.

541
00:25:58,350 --> 00:26:00,435
"I gave up on it once.

542
00:26:01,186 --> 00:26:03,897
I went back."
He's so cool!

543
00:26:06,233 --> 00:26:08,944
So perfectly balanced.

544
00:26:09,027 --> 00:26:13,031
-His pentagon diagram would be perfect.
-Beautiful.

545
00:26:13,115 --> 00:26:16,409
When Tamosan said,
"So this is how you got your girl."

546
00:26:16,493 --> 00:26:18,245
His reaction wasn't,

547
00:26:18,328 --> 00:26:20,497
"No, I don't do that!"

548
00:26:20,581 --> 00:26:22,457
But, "Maybe it was."

549
00:26:22,541 --> 00:26:24,585
-So good.
-That was good.

550
00:26:24,668 --> 00:26:27,921
-It was really good.
-He's in a bubble. He can do anything.

551
00:26:28,839 --> 00:26:30,173
-Anything.
-Everything.

552
00:26:30,257 --> 00:26:32,551
-Everything he does is good.
-True.

553
00:26:32,635 --> 00:26:35,137
Apparently he's always pale.

554
00:26:36,096 --> 00:26:37,430
I don't mind that at all!

555
00:26:37,515 --> 00:26:39,517
I'm totally with you.

556
00:26:40,475 --> 00:26:42,561
So this is the bubble!

557
00:26:42,645 --> 00:26:44,813
-We've seen this happen a few times.
-We have.

558
00:26:44,897 --> 00:26:49,527
We've seen it a few times,
but I knew the mask would come off.

559
00:26:49,610 --> 00:26:52,696
-This time, it's the real deal.
-It may be the real deal.

560
00:26:52,780 --> 00:26:55,240
In the past,
even if everyone fussed over someone,

561
00:26:55,323 --> 00:26:56,909
I knew it wouldn't last.

562
00:26:56,992 --> 00:26:58,827
-I had a sixth sense.
-Yeah.

563
00:26:58,911 --> 00:27:03,206
Also, the bubble tends to burst

564
00:27:03,290 --> 00:27:05,751
when relationships get involved.

565
00:27:05,834 --> 00:27:08,712
Their quirks tend to come out,
and the bubble usually bursts.

566
00:27:09,337 --> 00:27:12,007
-So we'll see if that'll happen here.
-That's right.

567
00:27:12,090 --> 00:27:15,678
-But Nacchan's facial expression...
-She likes him.

568
00:27:15,761 --> 00:27:17,387
-Right?
-She likes him.

569
00:27:17,470 --> 00:27:21,433
In the morning,
when Nacchan came back from jogging,

570
00:27:21,517 --> 00:27:24,061
and Hansan came to the sofa...

571
00:27:24,144 --> 00:27:30,776
And then she says, "I went for a jog,"
and sort of leaps from the sofa.

572
00:27:30,859 --> 00:27:33,153
That behavior...
It was very girly.

573
00:27:33,236 --> 00:27:35,447
-It was.
-She leapt.

574
00:27:35,531 --> 00:27:37,407
She seemed excited.

575
00:27:37,490 --> 00:27:40,786
Completely different from
when she was arguing at the sink before.

576
00:27:40,869 --> 00:27:42,037
She said if she fell,

577
00:27:42,120 --> 00:27:44,665
it wouldn't matter
if he had a girlfriend or not.

578
00:27:44,748 --> 00:27:47,835
-So I'm sure she'll come on strong.
-I'm sure.

579
00:27:47,918 --> 00:27:51,338
-I want to see how he evades those moves.
-Me too.

580
00:27:51,421 --> 00:27:54,216
-He's gonna say something good.
-Yes, he will.

581
00:27:54,299 --> 00:27:55,968
-I want to see it.
-He's going to deftly decline.

582
00:27:56,051 --> 00:27:57,678
-I'm sure of it.
-I want to see!

583
00:27:57,761 --> 00:28:02,182
Like, in a way that shows his sincerity.

584
00:28:03,141 --> 00:28:04,267
Yeah.

585
00:28:04,351 --> 00:28:08,271
With no false niceness from him.
Nothing fake.

586
00:28:09,481 --> 00:28:11,942
Like, I'd want to be rejected this way.

587
00:28:12,025 --> 00:28:13,861
You're totally seeing Hansan
from a female perspective.

588
00:28:16,488 --> 00:28:20,408
Let's watch.
I want to see Handa.

589
00:28:26,289 --> 00:28:28,083
-Welcome back.
-Hey.

590
00:28:29,334 --> 00:28:30,335
Hey.

591
00:28:32,129 --> 00:28:34,798
-They're smiling.
-What?

592
00:28:38,552 --> 00:28:40,428
What movie did you guys watch?

593
00:28:41,471 --> 00:28:43,056
-Nothing.
-Oh, really?

594
00:28:44,517 --> 00:28:46,184
Hansan will be home soon.

595
00:28:46,268 --> 00:28:48,562
Hansan said he'll be back at 11:30 p.m.

596
00:28:48,646 --> 00:28:50,648
The two of them went to the studio today.

597
00:28:50,731 --> 00:28:52,065
-I went, too.
-Arman went, too.

598
00:28:52,149 --> 00:28:53,776
You were there, too?

599
00:28:53,859 --> 00:28:56,654
-I thought it was just the two of you.
-I see.

600
00:28:56,737 --> 00:28:58,989
Did they say I wasn't there?

601
00:28:59,948 --> 00:29:02,159
You weren't mentioned, Arman,

602
00:29:02,242 --> 00:29:04,828
-since you drove.
-So you went, too?

603
00:29:05,453 --> 00:29:07,330
I need to use the bathroom.

604
00:29:08,248 --> 00:29:11,752
-Do you want water, Arisa?
-I'll get it myself.

605
00:29:13,879 --> 00:29:15,548
I'm tired of this drink.

606
00:29:17,340 --> 00:29:18,592
There's Aoyama.

607
00:29:18,676 --> 00:29:19,718
-What?
-Aoyama.

608
00:29:19,802 --> 00:29:21,219
-What was it?
-Awamori?

609
00:29:26,349 --> 00:29:29,144
Hansan's running late.

610
00:29:29,227 --> 00:29:31,814
-What time is it?
-11:40 p.m.

611
00:29:35,818 --> 00:29:37,360
What I was going to say...

612
00:29:38,278 --> 00:29:39,613
What is it?

613
00:29:40,322 --> 00:29:42,866
Do you seriously want
to go somewhere on the bike?

614
00:29:42,950 --> 00:29:44,242
-Sure.
-You want to go?

615
00:29:44,326 --> 00:29:47,746
-Where?
-You can pick.

616
00:29:47,830 --> 00:29:50,624
-If you don't care where, I can pick.
-I don't care where.

617
00:29:52,125 --> 00:29:53,418
You're okay on the back of a bike?

618
00:29:53,502 --> 00:29:55,295
-The back?
-You're not riding on the back?

619
00:29:55,378 --> 00:29:56,755
-We're taking the bike, right?
-Yeah.

620
00:29:56,839 --> 00:29:57,965
-Are you driving?
-Wait, what?

621
00:29:58,048 --> 00:30:00,217
-You riding behind me, right?
-Yeah.

622
00:30:01,134 --> 00:30:03,428
Then I'll decide where.
When are you free?

623
00:30:03,512 --> 00:30:05,556
-You're mostly free, right?
-Mostly free.

624
00:30:05,639 --> 00:30:08,308
-What do you mean I'm mostly free?
-Because you are.

625
00:30:08,391 --> 00:30:09,893
I am mostly free.

626
00:30:09,977 --> 00:30:11,979
I'll ask you on a day I'm free.

627
00:30:12,081 --> 00:30:14,335
I'm going to ask you when you're free.

628
00:30:14,439 --> 00:30:17,192
Okay.
It can be anywhere.

629
00:30:17,275 --> 00:30:19,402
Far or close.

630
00:30:19,903 --> 00:30:21,614
Is there something you want to do?

631
00:30:22,531 --> 00:30:24,157
I'll leave it to you.

632
00:30:26,577 --> 00:30:28,495
You were thinking "What a hassle!"
just now, weren't you?

633
00:30:28,579 --> 00:30:30,413
-I wasn't.
-You're lying.

634
00:30:30,497 --> 00:30:32,457
-It's easier when it's up to me.
-Really?

635
00:30:32,541 --> 00:30:35,418
I can do whatever I want, right?

636
00:30:35,503 --> 00:30:36,587
That's right.

637
00:30:37,546 --> 00:30:39,673
-Then I leave it to you.
-Okay.

638
00:30:40,508 --> 00:30:41,509
Okay.

639
00:30:42,968 --> 00:30:45,012
I'll be looking forward to it.

